      <scopecontent id="aspace_e48d121398f898f6064b504339e6e13b">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of "problem books" - assignments set by Yale's graphic design faculty of graphic design "problems" to be creatively solved. The collection includes problems set by Paul Rand, Sheila Levrant de Bretteville, Pamela Hovland, Julian Bittiner, Barbara Glauber, John Gambell, and others. In addition to descriptions of problems and assignments, problem books may contain syllabi, readings, and other course materials.</p>
      </scopecontent>
